OL,3,CNo nationwide smartphone ban in Welsh
OL,4,Cschools, report recommends
OL,6,F"The more evidence we heard, the
OL,7,Fclearer it became that the
OL,8,Frelationship between young people and
OL,9,Ftheir phones is not simple.
OL,11,F"There are children who experience
OL,12,Fdistraction, cyber-bullying, addiction
OL,13,Fand anxiety delivered through their
OL,14,Fphones.
OL,16,F"There are others who are liberated by
OL,17,Fbeing able to manage health conditions
OL,18,For feel emboldened to walk to school,
OL,19,Fknowing they can always contact a
OL,20,Fparent.
